# Auto push updates

When finishing a batch of work that leaves local changes ready to ship:

1. Commit with a concise message that matches this repo’s style.
2. Push to `origin` on the current branch.
3. Do **not** ask “say push if you want this on GitHub” — just push.

Still follow the normal git safety rules (no force-push to main/master, no amending others’ commits, no secrets). If push fails (auth/network), report the error once.
